race.comment: GLOBAL ECLIPSE (6) has had a few chances this time in but is knocking on the door and finds a nice race. He's finished runner-up at his past three, beaten at Yarra Valley last time out as favourite but gets a significant jockey switch with Ethan Brown going aboard while also dropping in weight. He'll be in the first couple and take catching. SCINTILLANTE (2) is the danger. He's been okay without really threatening this time in, just battling home late when getting too far back. This is winnable, he just needs to settle closer if possible. TAKEMETOTHEMOON (12) battled well to score narrowly last time and can measure up while SPARKLE LINK (11) is ready to find her best form third up.
